    <div id="artwork-details">
        <div id="tombstone">
   
    <p><strong>Bibliography: Irving Penn Bibliography (English-language only)</strong><br />       <p>This selected bibliography contains materials in English that pertain to Irving Penn&#39;s life and career, including books by Penn, about Penn, exhibition catalogs, reviews, and more. The bibliography also includes information on primary source collections related to Penn and selected <em>Vogue</em> articles by and about Irving Penn. See also the <a href="../resource/1975">Irving Penn Bibliography of foreign language material</a>. For more information on the books that Irving Penn published, please see the theme essay on <a href="../book">Book Projects</a>.</p><br /><br />
    	     	    </p>

    </div><!--/tombstone-->
    </div><!--/artwork-details-->
        <div id="artwork-body">

                		<p><a name="top"></a>

<p><a href="1976#biblio">Bibliography</a> | <a href="1976#vogue"><em>Vogue</em> Articles</a> | <a href="1976#primary">Primary Source Collections</a></p>

<a name="biblio"></a>
<strong>Bibliography</strong><br><br>

Auchincloss, Eve. 1990. "Master of Light." <em>Connoisseur</em> 220 (May), p. 25.<br><br>

The Art Directors Club of New York. 1957. <em>Art Directing for Visual Communication and Selling</em>. Visual Communication Books/Hastings House.<br><br>

The Art Directors Club of New York. 1959. <em>The Art Director at Work: How 15 Medal-winning Exhibits Were Conceived and Executed</em>. Visual Communications Books/Hastings House.<br><br>

Auer, Michael and Mich&egrave;le Auer. 1985. <em>Photographers Encyclopaedia International 1939 to the Present</em>. Editions Camera Obscura.<br><br>

Bailey, David and Martin Harrison. 1985. <em>Shots of Style: Great Fashion Photos</em>. Exh. cat. Victoria and Albert Museum.<br><br>

Baker, Kenneth. 2005. &ldquo;Nudes Emerge from Wads of Chewing Gum.&rdquo; <em>San Francisco Chronicle</em> (January 8).<br><br>

Beaton, Cecil and Gail Buckland. 1975. <em>The Magic Image: The Genius of Photography from 1839 to the Present Day</em>. Weidenfeld and Nicolson.<br><br>

Bernheimer, Blanca. 2011. <em>Irving Penn: Ethnos</em>. Exh. cat. Bernheimer Fine Art Photography.<br><br>

Bourdon, David. 1974. &ldquo;People of the World Materialize in the Ambulant Studio of a Famous Photographer.&rdquo; <em>Smithsonian Magazine</em> 5, 7 (October), pp. 52&ndash;59.<br><br>

Boxer, Sarah. 2002. &ldquo;Irving Penn.&rdquo; <em>Artforum International</em> 40, 8 (April), p. 132.

Brodovitch, Alexey. 1964. <em>Alexey Brodovitch Worhshop [Workshop] Session Notes: Design Laboratory, including the Richard Avedon/Irving Penn session, n.d</em>. Photocopy from the Museum of Modern Art.<br><br>

Cocks, Jay. 1988. <em>Issey Miyake Photographs by Irving Penn</em>. Exh. cat. New York Graphic Society Books.<br>

Coleman, A. D. 1979. &ldquo;Visual Recycling: Irving Penn&#39;s &lsquo;Street Material.&amp;4quo;&rdquo; In <em>Light Readings: A Photography Critic's Writings 1968&ndash;1978</em>. Oxford University Press.<br><br>

Chua, Lawrence. 1989. &ldquo;Penn, Ritts, Weber.&rdquo; <em>Flash Art</em> 145 (March/April), p. 110.<br><br>

Crisler, Richard. 1990. &ldquo;Irving Penn.&rdquo; <em>New Art Examiner</em> 17 (June), pp. 51&ndash;52.<br><br>

Dalmacio, Edward Anthony. 1980. <em>History of Fashion Photography</em>. California State University Press.<br><br>

Delano, Sharon. 1999. &ldquo;Variations.&rdquo; <em>New Yorker</em> (August 16), pp. 70&ndash;75.<br><br>

Devlin, Polly. 1979. <em>Vogue Book of Fashion Photography</em>. Thames and Hudson.<br><br>

Edwards, Owen. 1980. &ldquo;The Nude According to Penn.&rdquo; <em>American Photographer</em> 5 (September), pp. 34&ndash;41.<br><br>

Edwards, Owen. 1977. &ldquo;Perspectives of Penn.&rdquo; <em>New York Times Magazine</em> (September 4), pp. 18&ndash;22.<br><br>

Eisler, Colin. 1979. &ldquo;Out of Vogue: Penn and Avedon&#39;s Salons de Refuse.&rdquo; <em>Art International</em> 22, 9 (February), pp. 35&ndash;37.<br><br>

Eisler, Colin. 2010. <em>Arch&aelig;ology</em>. Exh. cat. Pace/MacGill Gallery.<br><br>

Feliciano, Kristina. 2000. &ldquo;Penn and the Ultimate Product Shot.&rdquo; <em>Photo District News</em> 20, 11 (November), pp. 66&ndash;69.<br><br>

Florescu, Michael. 1982. &ldquo;Banquet of the Spirit.&rdquo; <em>Camera Arts</em> 2, 5 (September), pp. 54&ndash;63.<br><br>

Foerstner, Abigail. 1991. &ldquo;Irving Penn Portraits Document the Subject and the Artist.&rdquo; <em>Chicago Tribune</em> (March 29), p. 69.<br><br>

Foerstner, Abigail. 1995. &ldquo;A Master Gives his Archive to the Art Institute.&rdquo; <em>Chicago Tribune</em> (September 3), p. 7.<br><br>

Foresta, Merry A. and William F. Stapp. 1990. <em>Irving Penn: Master Images, The Collections of the National Museum of American Art and the National Portrait Gallery</em>. Exh. cat. Smithsonian Institution Press.<br><br>

Foundation Cartier pour l&rsquo;art contemporain, Paris. 1998. <em>Issey Miyake Making Things</em>. Exh. cat. Foundation Cartier pour l&rsquo;art contemporain/Scalo.<br><br>

Fraser, Kennedy. 1981. <em>The Fashionable Mind: Reflections on Fashion 1970&ndash;1982</em>. David R. Godine.<br><br>

Fraser, Kennedy. 1992. <em>On the Edge: Images from 100 Years of Vogue</em>. Random House.<br><br>

Friedl, Bettina. 2007. &ldquo;The Hybrid Art of Fashion Photography: American Photographers in Post-World II Europe.&rdquo; <em>Amerikastudien</em> [American Studies] 52, 1 pp. 47&ndash;62.<br><br>

Genocchio, Benjamin. &ldquo;Does Gum Lose its Flavor in a Photo?&rdquo; <em>New York Times</em> (November 14).<br><br>

George Eastman House and New York State Fair. 1964. <em>Photography &rsquo;64: An Invitational Exhibition</em>. Exh. cat. George Eastman House.<br><br>

Goldberg, Vicki. 1991. &ldquo;Irving Penn is Difficult. &lsquo;Can&#39;t You Tell&rsquo;.&rdquo; <em>New York Times</em> (November 24), pp. 39&ndash;49.<br><br>

Gordon, Morris and R. M. Del Val. 1965. &ldquo;IPEX, International Photographic Exposition 1965.&rdquo; <em>Camera</em> 44 (May), pp. 7&ndash;25.<br><br>

