<a name="primary"></a>
<strong>Primary Source Collections</strong><br><br>

<em><a>Irving Penn Archives</a></em>. Ryerson and Burnham Archives, Ryerson and Burnham Libraries, Art Institute of Chicago. Chicago, IL.<br><br>

There are surveys of Penn&#39;s work for <em>Vogue</em> in the Photography Study Room and the Irving Penn Paper Archives.
<ul>
	<li>Irving Penn: Vogue Survey September 1, 1968&ndash;May 1996 (Photography Study Room)</li>
	<li>Irving Penn: Vogue Survey October 1, 1948&ndash;August 15, 1968 (Photography Study Room)<br>
	<li>Vogue, American: Index of Penn's work featured in Vogue 1943&ndash;1965, compiled by Vogue (Box.FF 1.2.28)<br></li>
	<li>Vogue, American: Index of Penn's work featured in Vogue 1966&ndash;1985, compiled by Vogue (Box.FF 1.2.29)<br></li>
	<li>Vogue Survey: Index of Penn's work featured in Vogue October 1943&ndash;December 1998, compiled by staff of The Art Institute of Chicago (Box.FF 128.1-2)</li>
</ul>

Additionally, there is a small collection of miscellaneous ephemera in the Ryerson and Burnham Libraries pamphlet collection. <a href="http://ryerson.artic.edu/record=b192228~S1">Irving Penn, P-08008</a>.<br><br>

<em><a href="http://www.afs.org/archon/index.php?p=collections/controlcard&amp;id=14">The Irving Penn Photographic Collection, 1944&ndash;1945</a></em>. Archives of the American Field Service and AFS Intercultural Programs. New York, NY.<br><br>

